# Backend service boundaries (Node + general)

Apply only when the touched files are backend handlers, services, controllers, or API logic.

## Boundaries

- Separate transport (HTTP/RPC) from domain logic; keep auth, validation, and business rules in clear layers.
- Validate request/response boundaries explicitly; prefer consistent shapes for similar endpoints.
- Preserve async and module boundaries the repo already uses; avoid hidden cross-module side effects.

## Node.js (when stack is Node)

- Keep glue separate from core logic; avoid leaking secrets or env into client-visible errors.

## Contracts (API / handlers)

- Validate inputs and failure modes at boundaries; keep response shapes consistent for similar endpoints; avoid silent contract drift; update docs/schemas when contracts change.
